Although not known to be in any published dictionary the word Informationism is defined by some sources on the web as:

1. The use of information as a weapon.

2. Countering government propaganda.

3. Undermining Advertising.

[http://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=informationism urbandictionary.com]

In the book ''Habits of the High-Tech'' Heart Quentin Schultz defines it as “a non-discerning, vacuous faith in … information.” [http://www.ethicsdaily.com/article_detail.cfm?AID=1414 ethicsdaily.com/article]

"At present, informationism is considered a form of web-based terrorism, using blogs as a platform to initiate propagandist attacks. This definition, however is that generated by the post-modernist."

http://www.k0zzm0.com/philosophy/id5.html

There is also a blog called [http://www.theinformationist.com/ The Informationist] as well as a wiki site called [http://www.informationism.org informationism.org]